Determines how this destructible object should appear in the level editor.
Whether or not this object defines a separate prefab to be loaded on the server. This is not required and should be set to false in most cases.
Whether or not this object defines a separate prefab to be loaded in the editor.
Indicates that this object should not leave a footprint when baking terrain materials.
Overrides the material used for this object when rendering the level chart.
Indicates that fuel can be siphoned from this object. Use @Interactability with the 'Fuel' type instead.
Indicates that water can be siphoned from this object. Use @Interactability with the 'Fuel' type instead.
Indicates that vehicles should not take damage when colliding with this object.
Whether or not players should take fall damage when landing on this object.
Indicates that this object's collision should never be disabled in singleplayer.
Indicates that this object can not be hidden by culling volumes.
Determines how the 'interior' area is calculated for interior culling.
Multiplier for how far away objects within the 'interior' can be seen. This value is multiplied by 64 meters.
Position offset for the 'interior' area from the mesh bounds.
Size offset for the 'interior' area from the mesh bounds.
The collection of foliage that can be baked onto this object's surface.

Adds functionality to this object that changes the render queue position depending on whether or not the object is underwater. This fixes some transparency rendering issues when viewing the object through water.
Adds functionality to this object that enables a game object named 'Light' at night and disables it during the day.

Whether or not kill volumes should be added to any game objects named 'Kill' in this object's prefab. If the @Trigger prefab exists, the volumes will be added to children in that prefab instead of @Object.
Indicates that structures can be built on this object.
A default material palette that should be used to randomize the material of this object.
The minimum value of the Landmarks setting required for this object to be visible.
When set, the only holiday during which this object will be visible.
The object to replace this object with during the 'Christmas' holiday.
The object to replace this object with during the 'Halloween' holiday.
Whether or not this object is visible when the player has the Blood Spatters setting disabled.
Whether or not this object is excluded from the level batching process.

BundleAssets.Description: Prefab only loaded on the dedicated server. Should have collision but not renderers.
Prefab loaded on the client, and on the dedicated server unless @Has_Clip_Prefab is true.
Prefab loaded on the client, and on the dedicated server unless @Has_Clip_Prefab is true.
Prefab loaded on clients that is visible when the object is very far away.
Prefab used by NPCs to navigate around the object.
Prefab used to indicate where doors, windows, etc. should be able to be placed at.
Prefab used to add hard-coded triggers such as kill triggers to the object.

Localization.Description: Localized name of the object in the editor.
A line in this object's note.
Custom text when interacting with the object.

Values.Description: Larger objects and buildings that make up the level.
Medium objects that fill out the layout of large objects.
Smaller objects used for clutter and decoration.
NPCs that the player can interact or trade with.
A flat texture that overlays other surfaces.
Not interactable. Better to exclude the property completely.
These objects will change between their two states when interacted with – such as an open or closed door.
These objects can spawn items when interacted with.
These objects can display lines of text when interacted with.
These objects can be siphoned for water.
These objects can be siphoned for fuel.
These objects are destructible. It is preferable to use @Rubble 'Destroy' instead of @Interactability 'Rubble'.
These objects can provide access to dialogue, quests, and vendors.
These objects can be interacted with, but unlike other options they have no additional functionality.
These objects open the dialogue screen - similar to NPCs - with a non-NPC appearance and custom interact text.
"Open [F]" or "Close [F]" message.
"On [F]" or "Off [F]" message.
"Light [F]" or "Extinguish [F]" message.
"Start [F]" or "Stop [F]" message.
"Use [F]" message.
Custom text pulled from the @($local$::SDG.Unturned.ObjectAsset, Assembly-CSharp::Interact) property. The interact key is formatted into {0}.
Power is not required to interact with this object.
Power is required to toggle this object but once it's toggled power is not required for it to stay that way.
Power is required for this object to be enabled, and losing power will disable the object.
The object's default state will be shown in the editor.
The object's toggled state will be shown in the editor.
State doesn't affect AI collision.
AI collision is blocked when object state is ON.
AI collision is blocked when object state is OFF.
Create a material instance for child renderer of Toggle game object. Downside of this is exclusion from level batching texture atlas.
Object does not have any toggleable emissive materials.
Destruction of rubble sections does not affect whether Nav game object is active or not.
AI collision is blocked when any sections are alive. Once all sections are dead AI collision is unblocked.
No rubble. This shouldn't be used.
Each section of rubble can be individually destroyed.
The object's rubble sections should be alive when viewed in the editor.
The object's rubble sections should be destroyed when viewed in the editor. An optional 'Editor' object can be placed in the root level of the 'Object' prefab which will be visible in it's place.
The object does not participate in interior culling.
The interior is determined using the bounds of the mesh.
The interior is determined using the bounds of all Occlusion Area components on the object.
The object is always visible.
The object is visible when the Landmarks setting is at least 'Low'.
The object is visible when the Landmarks setting is at least 'Medium'.
The object is visible when the Landmarks setting is at least 'High'.
The object is only visible when the Landmarks setting is set to 'Ultra'.
